Popcru is calling for an increase in the danger allowance of prison and health officials. It says many work in unsavoury conditions, which have deteriorated during the COVID-19 pandemic. Popcru's Richard Mamabolo discusses this. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Popcru is calling for an increase in the danger allowance of prison and health officials. The organisation said many work in unsavoury conditions, which have deteriorated during the COVID-19 pandemic. READ: COVID-19: SAPS says services to continue if police stations close The union said considering the dire conditions these officers find themselves in, their danger pay should be reviewed. Police Minister Bheki Cele said the pandemic is straining the already stretched resources of the police service. READ: Sapu worried about COVID-19 cases among SAPS members Popcru's Richard Mamabolo said they've been observing members' working conditions. "Members work under difficult and strenuous conditions," he said.